<item>
            <title>[WICKET-5237] Wicket generates invalid HTML by expanding col tags</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-5237</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just noticed that wicket expands col tags, even though the (x)html specifications forbids it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;take this markup as an example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;table&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;colgroup&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;col width=&quot;20%&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;col width=&quot;80%&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/colgroup&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;tbody&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;tr&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;td&amp;gt;I take a fifth of the available space&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;td&amp;gt;I take four fifth of the available space&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/tr&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/tbody&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/table&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead of return this as-is, it get&apos;s converted to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;table&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;colgroup&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;col width=&quot;20%&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/col&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;col width=&quot;80%&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/col&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/colgroup&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;tbody&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;tr&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;td&amp;gt;I take a fifth of the available space&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;td&amp;gt;I take four fifth of the available space&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/tr&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/tbody&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/table&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the specifications mention that col tags must not have end tags. This may be related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-2765&quot; title=&quot;MarkupException on unclosed &amp;lt;col&amp;gt; tag&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-2765&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-2765&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, as this seems to be the point when col was added to the OpenCloseTagExpander class. Note that it is ok to have a non closing col tag in html (self-closing in xhtml). It&apos;s all about generating a separated end tag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This happens in wicket 6.8, but I guess it&apos;s relevant to all versions down to wicket 1.4.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Specs for reference:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/1999/REC-html401-19991224/struct/tables.html#edef-COL&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/TR/1999/REC-html401-19991224/struct/tables.html#edef-COL&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/html-markup/col.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/TR/html-markup/col.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Kind regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Konrad&lt;/p&gt;</description>
